WEBVTT

00:09.898 --> 00:12.498
<i>English,</i> for a girl who
wants to study in America.

00:12.538 --> 00:14.438
Hey, my English is as good as yours.

00:15.372 --> 00:16.650
Three weeks away,

00:16.652 --> 00:18.942
and I still don't have my dream dress.

00:20.045 --> 00:21.645
We discussed it,

00:21.647 --> 00:23.914
and because it's a
once-in-a-lifetime event...

00:23.916 --> 00:26.717
and only 'cause it's
a once-in-a-lifetime event...

00:26.719 --> 00:28.585
you may spend 500.

00:28.587 --> 00:32.356
And that's shoes and
everything else included.

00:32.357 --> 00:34.358
And no negotiation.

00:34.360 --> 00:37.027
Okay, but... What did I say

00:37.029 --> 00:38.695
about negotiation? But this night will

00:38.697 --> 00:40.596
literally go down in history.

00:41.118 --> 00:42.833
And we can afford it.

00:42.835 --> 00:44.001
Mom,

00:44.528 --> 00:46.492
you can pick five of those
“formative books”

00:46.494 --> 00:48.365
you want me to read. I'll have them done

00:48.367 --> 00:49.640
by my birthday for shoes separate.

00:51.399 --> 00:52.898
Okay,

00:52.900 --> 00:54.299
have it your way.

00:54.301 --> 00:56.335
Eight books, English,

00:56.337 --> 01:00.205
at my discretion,
for 500, shoes separate.

01:00.207 --> 01:01.306
Six.

01:04.278 --> 01:05.611
Ah, I have to...

01:05.613 --> 01:07.246
- Got to go.
- Got to go.

01:07.248 --> 01:08.580
Yep.

01:09.704 --> 01:11.904
Bye, Mommy.

